      • setEquivalentObjects

        public void setEquivalentObjects(java.util.Set<org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLObject> objects)
        Sets equivalent objects for the object being rendered. For example, if the object being rendered is A, and B and C are equivalent to A, then setting the equivalent objects to {B, C} will cause the rendering to have (= B = C) appended to it
        Parameters:
        objects - The objects that are equivalent to the object being rendered
